      "side": 1,
      "message": "There is only one GM (HSL_duck) that\u0027s still producing different results (nothing drastic, though). From investigation, it\u0027s because of how I did this - we\u0027re now getting modulation by a uniform uploaded directly to the fragment shader, rather than a varying color coming from the GP. Presumably the varying has lower precision? I could change this to still put the color on the paint and inject the Xfermode::Modulate, I just figured the uniform version was clearer, given the constraints here?",
      "revId": "9bce11fc1fd0359b814d6cf8246f96e6a83c0186",
